modName: UNP - Ultra Skimpy Armor by Nightasy
summary: Ultra Skimpy Armor for UNP Normal. Work in Progress.
descriptionHtml:
SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT
Texture and Mesh modding in TESO
Go to this link and show your support!!!
http://forums.bethsoft.com/topic/1426220-client-side-customization/


Behold! A new law is decreed in Skyrim that all woman should be required to wear skimpy clothing. Thus the fashion designer Nightasy steps from the shadows to save the land!!!

This mod is an armor replacer.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ultra Skimpy Armors Available:
Nightingale Armor
Stormcloak Armor One
Stormcloak Armor Two
Iron Armor
Banded Iron Armor
Leather Armor
Steel Armor Light
Steel Armor Heavy
Elven Armor Light
Elven Armor Heavy
Dwarven Armor
Glass Armor
Orcish Armor
Imperial Armor Light
Imperial Armor Heavy
Nordic Plate Armor
Ebony Armor
Thieves Guild Armor
Blades Armor
Hide Armor Light
Hide Armor Medium
Hide Armor Heavy
Hide Armor Chieftain
Falmer Armor
Bandit Armor One
Bandit Armor Two
Bandit Armor Three
Dark Brotherhood Shrouded Armor
Savior's Hide Armor
Dragon Bone Armor
Dragon Scale Armor
Draugr Armor
Ebony Mail Armor
Wolf Armor
Sons of Talos Armor
General Tulius Armor

Ultra Skimpy Clothing Available:
Mage Apprentice
Mage Journeyman

NEXT UP!
Revisions, any missed armors and clothing.


Heads up! All of these armors have working weight sliders.


Requires UNP - Normal. Download it here:
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=6709

Special Thanks to Bethesda, Nifskope, Autodesk, Niftools (Figment), FOMM (Timeslip), GIMP
Special Thanks to Dimonized for creating the UNP model.
Special Thanks to Anano for letting me use his Layer Bikini mesh.
Special Thanks to Hentai for the use of his Void Armor leggings.
Special Thanks to Beeex.net for their Photoshop Tutorials.

Future Plans for Modding:
Making more sexy armor for UNP.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IF YOU USE THE HIGH RES TEXTURE PACK YOU MAY HAVE TO DO THIS IF IT DOES NOT FIX YOUR ISSUE! ONLY DO THIS IF AFTER INSTALLING THE TEXTURE PACK/PACKS YOUR PROBLEM STILL EXISTS! BE SURE TO BACKUP THE INI's.

TheOutlander @ Nexus forum

1. Disable the esps that came with the official texture pack.

2. Backup then open
SteamAppsCommonSkyrimSkyrim_default.ini
&
DocumentsMy GamesSkyrimSkyrim.ini

3. Change this in both files: (There are usually two seperate lines in the Archive section. Only change the one listed below or you will lose NPC sound.)
[Archive]
sResourceArchiveList=Skyrim - Misc.bsa, Skyrim - Shaders.bsa, Skyrim - Textures.bsa, Skyrim - Interface.bsa, Skyrim - Animations.bsa, Skyrim - Meshes.bsa, Skyrim - Sounds.bsa

To this:
[Archive]
sResourceArchiveList=Skyrim - Misc.bsa, Skyrim - Shaders.bsa, Skyrim - Textures.bsa, Skyrim - Interface.bsa, Skyrim - Animations.bsa, Skyrim - Meshes.bsa, Skyrim - Sounds.bsa, HighResTexturePack01.bsa, HighResTexturePack02.bsa

4. Save both files.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version Release:
5.0 - Complete Graphical Revamping of all available Armors.
------ Removed NPC commoner clothing.
------ Added First Person View to all Armors.
4.1 - Bandit Zero Armor: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Bandit One Armor: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Bandit Two Armor: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Bandit Three Armor: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Ebony Armor: Repaired Texture Effect. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Imperial Armor Heavy: Fixed Vertices Weights.
4.0 - Nordic Plate: Fixed texture effects. Added texture effect to under garment.
------ Imperial Armor Light: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Imperial Armor Medium: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Imperial Armor Heavy: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Blades Armor: Fixed texture effects. Updated Body Mesh.
3.95 - Dwarven Armor: Fixed the armor not appearing on low weight slide settings. Fixed vertex weights.
------ Added High Res Armor Texture Pack under Misc Downloads.
------ Added High Res Clothing Texture Pack under Misc Downloads.
------ Added Cube Map Texture Pack under Misc Downloads.
3.9 - Added Blacksmith Clothing.
------ Dragonscale Armor: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Iron Armor: Complete Rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Wolf Armor: Removed Shoulders. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Dwarven Armor: Updated Body Mesh.
3.8 - Hide Armor: Lower rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Barkeeper Clothing: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Farmer One Clothing: Updated Body Mesh. Re-Added the undergarment texture.
------ Merchant Clothing: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Wench Clothing: Updated Body Mesh.
3.75 - Leather Armor: Re-textured leggings and removed shine.
------ Mage Apprentice: Changed the boots to shoes so they work with Mage Journeyman.
3.7 - Stormcloak One: Complete rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Stormcloak Two: Complete rework. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Mage Journeyman: Complete rework.
------ Ebony Mail: Updated Body Mesh. Fixed blocky look.
------ Elven Armor: Updated Body Mesh. Fixed gloves collision.
3.6 - Added Mage Journeyman clothing.
------ Leather Armor: Completely reworked from the ground up. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Steel Armor Light: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Steel Armor Heavy: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Nordic Plate Armor: Updated Body Mesh.
3.5 - Added Mage Apprentice clothing.
------ Nightingale Armor: Changed Undergarment. Fixed Weight Slider. Updated Body Mesh. Fixed Leggings Collision.
------ Glass Armor: Removed Leggings. Updated Body Mesh.
------ Draugr Armor: Updated Body Mesh.
------ Ebony Armor: Updated Body Mesh
3.4 - Added Wolf gear, Sons of Talos gear and General Tulius gear.
3.3 - Added Ebony Mail gear, Merchant clothing and Wench clothing.
3.2 - Added Draugr gear, Farmer Four clothing and Barkeeper clothing.
3.1 - Added Dragon Scale gear, Farmer Three clothing and Farmer Three Plus clothing.
3.0 - Added Dragon Bone gear, Farmer One clothing and Farmer Two clothing.
2.9 - Added Savior's Hide gear.
2.8 - Added Dark Brotherhood Shrouded gear.
2.7 - Added Bandit gear.
2.6 - Added Falmer gear.
2.5 - Added Hide gear.
2.4 - Added Blades gear.
2.3 - Added Thieves Guild gear.
2.2 - Added Ebony gear.
2.1 - Added Nordic Plate gear.
2.0 - Added Light and Heavy Imperial gear.
1.9 - Added Orcish gear.
1.8 - Added Glass gear.
1.7 - Added Dwarven gear.
1.6 - Added Light and Heavy Elven gear.
1.5 - Added Light and Heavy Steel gear.
1.4 - Added Leather gear.
1.3 - Added Iron and Banded Iron gear.
1.2 - Added Stormcloak gear.
1.1 - Fixed Transparency issue on the Nightengale Armor looks much better now.
1.0 - Initial Release.
